---
# Which profile is live. Must name a key under profiles: below; a name with
# no matching key contributes no overrides and everything falls back to
# skill/agent frontmatter defaults.
# The BPE_PROFILE environment variable, when set, overrides this field in
# every settings file (shell-scoped switching: `BPE_PROFILE=work claude`).
active_profile: personal

# Named profiles. Names are yours to choose; `personal` and `work` are the
# conventional pair. Each profile carries optional skills: and agents: maps.
profiles:
  personal:
    # Skill overrides. Keys are bare skill names as they appear in
    # bpe/skills/<name>/SKILL.md (`brainstorm`, not `bpe:brainstorm`).
    # Values accept anything the SKILL.md model: field accepts: a family
    # alias (opus, sonnet, haiku) or an explicit pinned model ID.
    # Skills you leave out fall back to their frontmatter model: default,
    # so list only the overrides that differ.
    skills:
      brainstorm: claude-opus-4-7        # pinned ID: always this exact model
      apply-review: claude-opus-4-7
    # Agent overrides. Keys are bare agent names as they appear in
    # bpe/agents/<name>.md (`validator`, not `bpe:validator`).
    agents:
      validator: claude-opus-4-7
  work:
    skills:
      brainstorm: opus                    # alias: latest available Opus here
      apply-review: opus
    agents:
      validator: opus
---

# BPE Profile Settings

Copy this file to `~/.claude/bpe.local.md` (user-global) or to `.claude/bpe.local.md` at a repo root (per-project), dropping the `.example` suffix, then edit the frontmatter above.
The per-project file shadows the user-global one key by key: a lookup that misses in the per-project file falls through to the user-global file before falling back to frontmatter.
The active profile name is resolved once (BPE_PROFILE, else the per-project file's `active_profile`, else the user-global file's) and selects the profile in both files.

This body is free-form notes; model resolution reads only the frontmatter.

The real settings file is user-local state.
Never commit it: add `.claude/*.local.md` to your `.gitignore`.

Canonical schema and lookup precedence: `bpe/references/model-profiles.md` in the BPE plugin.
